"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Pulsed wave Doppler echocardiogram in mitral stenosis",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 387px; height: 248px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Pulsed wave Doppler in a patient with mitral stenosis shows reduced diastolic flow after the E point (ie, reduced E-F slope), indicating reduced excursion of the mitral valve leaflet. The peak velocity is increased to over 2 m/sec, translating into a transvalvular gradient of 16 mmHg. There is also an increase in the amplitude of the A wave.",
